{
  "texts": [
    "Her usage of these terms is highly specific, because sharp and distinct definitions are necessary in order to operationalize these constructs and uncover their underlying mechanisms.",
    "Moreover, such specificity allows communicating scientific ideas efficiently among experts.",
    "But what if even scientists from related fields use these terms differently, and worse still, they are unaware of this fact?",
    "In that case, the psychologist's findings will most probably be misconstrued by, say, a neurophysiologist; only if the psychologist and neurophysiologist mean the same thing when they speak about attention and distraction will the psychologist's work be relevant for the neurophysiologist.",
    "The same holds for communication across the various subfields of psychology and many additional neighboring disciplines, such as computer science, philosophy, economics, and pedagogy."
  ]
}